This Double wide mobile is ready for some TLC. It would make a great rental, or even an awesome starter home. It is just outside of Duncan which makes it a great location for working at the mine or for nice trips to the Safford area. The country view is amazing with the river not to far from the home and it is a great area for 4 wheeling raising animals and horseback riding.

This 3.88-acre property offers a rare combination of self-sufficiency, investment potential, and natural beauty, complete with water access and stunning views of Steeple Rock. The land includes two irrigable acres with irrigation rights, accessed through a private irrigation gate, and a back entrance gate that allows easy truck access from the ditch road. A large pile of gravel on the property is ready to be used for future improvements or landscaping. Well water is available, and a brand-new septic system was installed in 2024, giving you a head start on essential infrastructure. The existing manufactured home needs renovation, offering the perfect opportunity for customization, whether you're an investor looking for value-add potential or a buyer wanting to create your own off-grid sanctuary. Inside, the home features a wood-burning stove for cozy heat in the cooler months. For those drawn to sustainable living, the property includes a thriving organic kitchen garden, two compost barrels inside the yard, and two additional compost piles outside the yard, making it ideal for gardening.
Cash only. This fixer upper has a lot of potential! Large home on an acre. Utilities are off, buyer may turn them on for inspections.

If you're looking for acreage and a newer home in Greenlee County, this is it!Come see this 2024 manufactured home, affixed and situated on 17.46 acres, offering a desirable split floor plan with 4 bedrooms and 2 baths. The home features block skirting, indirect interior lighting, and a spacious kitchen island ideal for added food prep and entertaining. Abundant windows throughout fill the home with natural light and showcase the beautiful surroundings.The property is well-suited for livestock, complete with an arena and holding pens, and includes a private well along with an RV hookup for added convenience. Enjoy wonderful mountain views and the added benefit of being within walking distance to the elementary school.A perfect blend of space, functionality, and peaceful country living.

Ideal for horse owners, the land provides ample grazing space. Additionally, it comes with decreed water rights and a sturdy 16 X 50 metal building that stands ready for your imagination. Whether it be for living or a large storage space. What's more, electricity, gas and water connections are readily available, providing modern conveniences for your comfort. This property holds endless potential for your dreams.

You can see for miles in all directions! This great 4BR 2.5BA home with an attached 3 car garage is available. Downstairs, get cozy by the fireplace in the living room right by the kitchen and dining area. There's a half bath and a couple closet pantries for storage. In back is a flex room that houses the laundry but has plenty of space for a large dining table or game tables or whatever needs you have. Upstairs, there are the 4 bedrooms along with the guest bath. The primary suite has two walk-in closets and a large vanity in the bathroom. The best thing about the room may be the direct access to the second floor patio on the west side of the home, a wonderful place to enjoy AZ sunsets! In fact, there is a porch or seating area at each side of the house giving you plenty of viewing options outside. There will also be new carpeting installed, likely early February.

Spacious 2,578 Sq Ft Home on 2.08 Acres in Duncan! This charming property features 2 bedrooms, 1 full bath, and two 3/4 baths across 2,578 sq ft of comfortable living space. The large living room boasts custom woodwork that adds warmth and character. A spacious custom kitchen includes a new electric cooktop, perfect for cooking and entertaining. The unfinished basement offers great potential for storage, a workshop, or future living space. A new tankless hot water heater serves part of the home, adding energy efficiency. Outside, a concrete walkway wraps around most of the house for easy access. With 2.08 acres of land, there's plenty of space for gardening, animals, or future expansion. Enjoy peaceful rural living, beautiful views, and small-town charm. Schedule your showing today-this one won't last!

This property is located at the intersection of North Campbell St. and Mesquite Ave. in Duncan, AZ. The seller is offering two large parcels of land, totaling 58.48 acres, which consist of one parcel with 38.48 acres and a second adjacent parcel of 20 acres, for a total of $235,000 for both parcels. While the seller is open to options, there is a strong preference to sell both parcels together. Conveniently situated just down the road from Duncan Junior High, these parcels can have access to essential utilities, including gas, electricity and water, which are available across the street. This land offers abundant potential for development. For more details and to explore the possibilities, please contact us today, don't miss this opportunity!

Great opportunity, 550 ACRES, two wells, and power available, it's definitely a prime spot for development or a private retreat. Duncan Arizona, is a great area with access to nature and still not to far from other towns, which could make it ideal for residential development. Residential development could be huge in the area!!!

Prime York Valley AZ location. Discover 8.16 acres of prime land in Greenlee County, will be split from parcel 300-31-009A at close of escrow. This property offers direct access off Highway 75-once you leave the highway, you're already on your land. A recorded 30' easement runs along the south side of the property, providing legal ingress and egress. Electric service is conveniently located along the highway just outside the property line. The sellers will complete grading and drainage work and provide an elevation study to ensure the land meets all required building and floodplain standards for future development. A new survey of the 8.16 acres will be provided at the seller's expense. CC&R's will apply to preserve quality standards, including Site-built homes only (no mobile homes)1-acre minimum lots No RV parks This is a rare opportunity to own easily accessible acreage with utilities nearby and sellers providing some development preparation. Ideal for a custom home site or small subdivision.
